title: Gibson ES-295 1952
description: A beautiful ES-295 with wear you can't fake! The ES-295 was originally produced from 1952 to 1958 and is best known for being the model played by Scotty Moore with Elvis. This particular example plays well with a fantastic feeling neck! The guitar has heavy finish wear with the beautiful greening that you often see on '50s goldtops. Glaser has refretted the guitar and replaced the tailpiece crossbar. The pickguard is missing.

title: Gibson ES-335 Dot 2013
description: You can't go wrong with a cherry ES-335! This Dot neck is a great playing guitar that is in excellent condition. Comes with the original hard case.

title: Gibson ES-339 New
description: The Gibson ES-339 is a modern classic designed for those seeking the tone and look of an ES-335, but desire a slightly smaller, lighter instrument. The pearloid dot inlay rosewood fingerboard on a hand-rolled Rounded C mahogany neck remind players where it all started. The all-new MHS II humbucking pickups paired with our hand-wired tone circuit showcases the versatile Gibson ES tone that players have craved for over 60 years. Tuning stability and precise intonation are provided by the Grover 'Milk Bottle' tuners, an ABR-1 bridge with brass saddles, and a Stopbar tailpiece. Impressive gloss finishes include Sixties Cherry, Light Caramel Burst, and Dark Natural.

title: Gibson Les Paul Pro 1978
description: This Les Paul Pro has a pair of P-90s and a black finish. The bridge has been replaced and there are screw-holes from a previous Bigsby.

title: Gibson Les Paul Traditional 2013
description: A modern take on the classic design. This '13 Les Paul Traditional both plays and sounds good making it a fantastic guitar for the money. The guitar is in excellent condition and comes with the original hard case.
specs: Body Wood - Mahogany w/ Maple Top

title: Gibson Les Paul Tribute 2017
description: A quality stripped down Les Paul featuring a satin gold top finish, trapezoid inlays, and a pair of humbuckers.
specs: Body Wood - Mahogany w/ Maple Cap

title: Gibson Custom Shop Les Paul 1959 Reissue CVG 2016
description: This is the 4th Les Paul made in a very limited run for Carter Vintage. The top was handpicked, the neck custom shaped, and the pickups wound to our spec by OX4. A light bourbonburst finish makes this a strikingly beautiful instrument! Comes with the original hard case.
specs: Body Wood - Mahogany w/ Bookmatched Flame Maple Top

title: Gibson Custom Shop SG '61 Reissue New Left Handed
description: A 1960s SG has been the favorite of some of the most iconic guitarists ever...Angus Young, Tony Iommi, Robby Krieger, George Harrison, Dickey Betts, Gary Rossington, and Eric Clapton, to name a few. The SG's devilish points and curves, blistering humbucker tone and fast-playing neck help to make it one of the most coveted and revered 1960s Gibson models. This Custom Shop Historic Reissue SG continues the legendary magic of the originals with all solid woods, historic hide-glue construction methods, the finest vintage replica parts and materials available and the instantly-recognizable, powerful tone of pure rock 'n roll.

title: Fender Esquire 1953
description: This all-original 1953 Esquire is one of the lightest Blackguards to come through the shop, weighing in at only 6.7lbs. The guitar is in excellent condition with only weather checking in the finish. Comes with the original hard case. The nut has been replaced.

title: Fender Stratocaster '59 Reissue
description: A quality '59 reissue Stratocaster. The guitar is in excellent condition and comes with the original brown hard case and case candy.

title: Fender Eric Johnson Stratocaster 2006
description: The Eric Johnson Stratocaster features a unique ’57-style soft V neck with a 12 radius. This particular EJ strat is has had the neck pickup replaced.

title: Fender Stratocaster 2004
description: This Mexican made Strat features a gold finish, gold anodized pickguard, and has been signed by Scotty Moore.

title: Fender Stratocaster Hendrix Voodoo 1997
description: This Jimmi Hendrix inspired strat has a reverse headstock and an Olympic White finish. Comes with the original hard case.

title: Fender Stratocaster Special Edition
description: This special edition Strat has '59 Specs and a thin-skin nitrocellulose lacquer finish that has been relic'd.

title: Fender Telecaster Custom '61 Reissue 1995
description: This Custom Shop model was made by Alex Perez and used by Audley Freed with  the Black Crows and Jimmy Page on Live from the Greek Theater and with Cry of Love on Diamonds and Debris. Comes with a w/ letter of authenticity and a gig bag.

title: Fender Custom Shop Telecaster Custom '61 NOS 2013
description: A tele that needs to be in a spotlight! This fantastic Tele Custom features a silver sparkle finish that is impossible to miss! While the finish may pull you in, it's the playability and sound that will keep this tele in your hands! The guitar is in excellent condition and comes with the original hard case.

title: Gretsch G5422T Electromatic 2013
description: This G5422T is in solid condition and features a pair of Blacktop Filter'Trons. A quality Korean made Gretsch. The pickguard is in the gig bag.

title: Gretsch Country Gentleman 2007
description: A great playing, Japanese made Country Gent. This version of the model features a double-cutaway body, Filter'Tron pickups, and a Bigsby vibrato. Comes with the original hard case.

title: Gretsch Roc Jet 1976
description: A nice example of a mid '70s Gretsch solidbody! This Roc Jet features a pair of Super'Tron pickups and a red stain finish. Comes with a non-original Gretsch hard case.

title: Gretsch Country Gentleman 2018
description: A beautiful rendition of the Country Gentleman! This Japanese made Gretsch features a natural finish over a flame maple top back and sides. The guitar is in excellent overall condition.

title: Gretsch Double Anniversary 1968
description: A quality example of a late '60s Double Anniversary. The guitar features a sunburst finish and is loaded with a pair of Hi-Lo'Tron pickups. Comes with the original hard case.

title: Gretsch G6128T George Harrison 2017
description: A great playing recreation on George Harrison's Duo-Jet! Staying true to the original, this reissue is loaded with a set of DynaSonic single-coil pickups. Comes with the original tweed case.

title: Gretsch Super Chet 1977
description: The Super Chet is a 17 inch hollowbody that was produced throughout the 70s. The guitar has a single cutaway with a body depth of 2 1/2. A pair of Filter'Tron pickups are controlled by 5 knobs that are all mounted on the pickguard.This particular example is in nice playing condition. There has been repair work on the knobs.

title: Gretsch Chet Atkins Hollow Body (6120) 1958
description: A classic 6120 Chet Atkins in excellent condition! This single-cut Grestch is loaded with its original filtertrons pickups which tonally sit perfectly between a humbucker and a tele. The finish is in beautiful condition with a faded orange color. Few guitars sound like a Gretsch and this is a prime example of their most popular model. This guitar was previously owned by Ed King.

title: Gibson J-45 Standard 2019
description: The J-45 is Gibson's best-selling acoustic of all time. Nicknamed The Workhorse and first introduced in 1942, this iconic acoustic has become the cornerstone of its round-shoulder, dreadnought line. World renowned for its full, balanced expression, warm bass and excellent projection, the J-45 has been refined to carry this legacy to new heights. This 2019 model delivers a sound with incredible dynamic range, warm mids, and a tight punchy bass.
specs: Pickup(s) - Under Saddle with Volume and Tone controls in soundhole

title: Martin OM-18 1933 Authentic 2015
description: A fantastic recreation of an early OM-18. The guitar features an Adirondack Spruce top over a mahogany back and sides.
